Quick definitions (mediate)


'''verb:'''   occupy an intermediate or middle position or form a connecting link or stage between two others (Example: "Mediate between the old and the new")
 
'''verb:'''   act between parties with a view to reconciling differences (Example: "He mediated a settlement")
 
'''adjective:'''   acting through or dependent on an intervening agency (Example: "The disease spread by mediate as well as direct contact")

'''adjective:'''   being neither at the beginning nor at the end in a series (Example: "In a mediate position")
